Jeanette Chabalala, News24(iStock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Kimberley &ndash; A 27-year-old man has been sentenced to 20 years in prison for the murder of his girlfriend, Northern Cape police said on Tuesday.&nbsp;&nbsp; Adam Lukas was sentenced in the Fraserburg Regional Court on Wednesday last week, said Lieutenant Colonel Dimakatso Mooi.&nbsp; He was arrested in September 2015 after the body of Jerinica Jacobs, 20, was found lying in a field just outside Fraserburg, said Mooi.&nbsp; "According to the information received, the victim was murdered on September 5, 2015. The suspect beat the victim to death and left her in the [field]," she said.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; "It was through a meticulous investigation conducted by Warrant Officer Fiks of Fraserburg Detectives, and proper gathering of forensic evidence, that led to a successful conviction."24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.